    {
      "id": "e8vPLud8yxo26slov5-k5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 184.94396257741585,
      "y": -121.09786766385815,
      "width": 1252.6793212890625,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aQ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1223825293,
      "version": 232,
      "versionNonce": 41936643,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775767651028,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Design Ticketmaster\n\nTicketmaster is an online platform that lets user purchase ticekts for concets, sport events, theater and other entertainment.\n\nHas ~ 100 M DAU [Daily Active Users]",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Design Ticketmaster\n\nTicketmaster is an online platform that lets user purchase ticekts for concets, sport events, theater and other entertainment.\n\nHas ~ 100 M DAU [Daily Active Users]",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "T2NdcaaYIxpfmAhN_HxOa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 200.45711907907958,
      "y": 253.85319409342492,
      "width": 1325.319091796875,
      "height": 450,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aT",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2075181517,
      "version": 1218,
      "versionNonce": 1945233773,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775919271379,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Requirement Analysis\n\nFunction Requirements [Features of the system]:\n1.  user should be able to book tickets. -> able to reserve a seat and book a event with some digital ticket.\n2. user should be able to view events. -> choose an event -> takes to event's page with details like destination, event date and prices.\n3. user should be able to search for events.  -> user searches an event, may be a drop down based on his choosen location.\n\n\nNon-Function Requirements [ the qualities of system, all \"ilities\" - scalabilities, availabilities etc ]:\n1. CAP theorm -> Prioritise Consistency >>> Availablity here -> 1 ticket must go to only 1 user. [ no double booking ]\n    - high availability for search and viewing events.\n2. Reads >> write -> lot people searching than few of them book.\n3. scalability to handle surges for popular events.\n4. low latency Search.\n\n-- out of scope -- \n1. user GDPR compliance.\n2. fault tolerance. etc...",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Requirement Analysis\n\nFunction Requirements [Features of the system]:\n1.  user should be able to book tickets. -> able to reserve a seat and book a event with some digital ticket.\n2. user should be able to view events. -> choose an event -> takes to event's page with details like destination, event date and prices.\n3. user should be able to search for events.  -> user searches an event, may be a drop down based on his choosen location.\n\n\nNon-Function Requirements [ the qualities of system, all \"ilities\" - scalabilities, availabilities etc ]:\n1. CAP theorm -> Prioritise Consistency >>> Availablity here -> 1 ticket must go to only 1 user. [ no double booking ]\n    - high availability for search and viewing events.\n2. Reads >> write -> lot people searching than few of them book.\n3. scalability to handle surges for popular events.\n4. low latency Search.\n\n-- out of scope -- \n1. user GDPR compliance.\n2. fault tolerance. etc...",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "IEPv8ls0BCNPuLjzx1PTv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1672.3970771904724,
      "y": -81.69102511324797,
      "width": 1084.619384765625,
      "height": 875,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aW",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 576379331,
      "version": 1711,
      "versionNonce": 252341005,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775768976358,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Core Entities and API\n\n1. Events\n2. Venue\n3. Perfromers/Artists.\n4. Tickets.\n\n\n1. API to view details of an Event\n\n    GET  /event/:eventId  -> Event & Venue & Performers & Available Tickets []\n\n2. API to search for an Event\n\n    GET  /search?term={term}&location={location}&type={type}&date={date} ->  Partial<Event>[]\n\n3. Book Ticket:\n    - 2 phase process:\n        1. First you select the seat of your choice.\n        2. You book the ticket on that seat with a timer. If timer runs out, the booked seat will be released.  \n    \n    POST /booking/reserve  -> this books the seat corresponding to a ticket and then user goes for payment.\n    {\n        ticketId\n    }\n\n    PATCH /booking/confirem\n    {\n        ticketId\n        paymentDetails ( Stripe )\n    }\n\n   NOTE:\n        - no userId or details mentioned in payload, as it will have a security impact.\n        - it usually sent through \"header\" in form of \"JWT / session token\"",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Core Entities and API\n\n1. Events\n2. Venue\n3. Perfromers/Artists.\n4. Tickets.\n\n\n1. API to view details of an Event\n\n    GET  /event/:eventId  -> Event & Venue & Performers & Available Tickets []\n\n2. API to search for an Event\n\n    GET  /search?term={term}&location={location}&type={type}&date={date} ->  Partial<Event>[]\n\n3. Book Ticket:\n    - 2 phase process:\n        1. First you select the seat of your choice.\n        2. You book the ticket on that seat with a timer. If timer runs out, the booked seat will be released.  \n    \n    POST /booking/reserve  -> this books the seat corresponding to a ticket and then user goes for payment.\n    {\n        ticketId\n    }\n\n    PATCH /booking/confirem\n    {\n        ticketId\n        paymentDetails ( Stripe )\n    }\n\n   NOTE:\n        - no userId or details mentioned in payload, as it will have a security impact.\n        - it usually sent through \"header\" in form of \"JWT / session token\"",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
