    },
    {
      "id": "_2clzQokIvRxn4uzLGk25",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 210.01375398493587,
      "y": 2421.0756189540093,
      "width": 1714.058837890625,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0J",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 370435085,
      "version": 1624,
      "versionNonce": 599115235,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775922628356,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Notes:\n\n- ElasticSeach Databases should not be used as primary Databases.\n   Reasons --> It mainly because of durability terms and handling complex transactions.\n- Then how we make sure our Primary DB is in sync with Elastic Search ?  -> Need to make sure any change in Primary DB must get propagated to Elasticsearch.\n    Ways:\n    \n    1.  You handle this from the application Code itself i.e any write in Promary DB also must update Elasticseach.\n        Cons: \n        Possible Consistency Problems. Whatif one of the write fails !\n    \n    2. Change Data Capture [CDC]\n        Any changes that happens to the Primary DB is put on a \"stream\" --> Then these change events can be consumed later. --> make use of it !\n        Cons:\n         It does have some limit -> as it is updating those indexes in elasticsearch.  -> Have to check the no of updates.\n    \n        In our case: The entities doesn;t change much like the events, perfromers, venue and all ---> So CDC is fine as our optimization for Sync Primary DB with Elasticsearch.\n\n            -> If More updates is there ---> Need to introduce a Queue -> Do batching of some sort to update the ElasticSearch.\n            ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Notes:\n\n- ElasticSeach Databases should not be used as primary Databases.\n   Reasons --> It mainly because of durability terms and handling complex transactions.\n- Then how we make sure our Primary DB is in sync with Elastic Search ?  -> Need to make sure any change in Primary DB must get propagated to Elasticsearch.\n    Ways:\n    \n    1.  You handle this from the application Code itself i.e any write in Promary DB also must update Elasticseach.\n        Cons: \n        Possible Consistency Problems. Whatif one of the write fails !\n    \n    2. Change Data Capture [CDC]\n        Any changes that happens to the Primary DB is put on a \"stream\" --> Then these change events can be consumed later. --> make use of it !\n        Cons:\n         It does have some limit -> as it is updating those indexes in elasticsearch.  -> Have to check the no of updates.\n    \n        In our case: The entities doesn;t change much like the events, perfromers, venue and all ---> So CDC is fine as our optimization for Sync Primary DB with Elasticsearch.\n\n            -> If More updates is there ---> Need to introduce a Queue -> Do batching of some sort to update the ElasticSearch.\n            ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
