    {
      "id": "8bGQ5a5mJE8Izwa1ccnzv",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1026.6295068726768,
      "y": 2125.939136145177,
      "width": 1172.359375,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0U",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2086159341,
      "version": 1090,
      "versionNonce": 910229187,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775922622643,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How do you take care of scaling ?\n\n-- The API Gateway we have, they have their own load balancers that take care of high incoming\ntraffic.\n-- The services have multiple instances running in parallel -> Each of them have their own load balancer\nthat handles the traffic through different instances of the service.\n-- For Databases:  We can have sharding  [ Horizontal Scaling ]\n    -> This also needs to be considered, do we need shard ? If too much events getting registerd across the globe\n        Probably yes !  \n        Then think of what to shard on ? Shard can be on event Ids or can be done based on geographically like venuID.\n   \n    Optional: \n    Since Reads  >>> Writes  --> WE need to reduce the reads on Postgress DB. \n    Can you Redis to cache the popular events may be !\n    \n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How do you take care of scaling ?\n\n-- The API Gateway we have, they have their own load balancers that take care of high incoming\ntraffic.\n-- The services have multiple instances running in parallel -> Each of them have their own load balancer\nthat handles the traffic through different instances of the service.\n-- For Databases:  We can have sharding  [ Horizontal Scaling ]\n    -> This also needs to be considered, do we need shard ? If too much events getting registerd across the globe\n        Probably yes !  \n        Then think of what to shard on ? Shard can be on event Ids or can be done based on geographically like venuID.\n   \n    Optional: \n    Since Reads  >>> Writes  --> WE need to reduce the reads on Postgress DB. \n    Can you Redis to cache the popular events may be !\n    \n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
